The search for 19-year-old University of Cape Town student Uyinene Mrwetyana continues. JOHANNESBURG - Western Cape police have arrested a 42-year-old man, following the disappearance of UCT student Uyinene Mrwetyana. The man was arrested in Claremont on Friday by SAPS and the Western Cape flying squad. WATCH: Friends hopeful missing UCT student will return home unharmed Police say they're confident that interviewing the man will lead to the finalisation of the investigation. The suspect will appear in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court on Monday. In the meantime, DNA tests and an autopsy are expected to be performed soon on an unidentified body discovered in Lingelethu West, Khayelitsha.